The paper focuses on the detection of Android malware using machine learning techniques, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The use of metadata and feature analysis also suggests a potential overlap with artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data science (cs.DS). The construction of classifiers for early detection may also relate to software engineering (cs.SE) and machine learning (cs.LG).
